{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629", "id": 428051691, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MjgwNTE2OTE=", "number": 59629, "title": "Thread locals keep Rust shared library from unloading `dlclose`.", "user": {"login": "Neopallium", "id": 68307, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY4MzA3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/68307?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium", "html_url": "https://github.com/Neopallium", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Neopallium/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 123110, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMjMxMTA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/O-linux", "name": "O-linux", "color": "6e6ec0", "default": false, "description": "Operating system: Linux"}, {"id": 632886930, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzI4ODY5MzA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-thread-locals", "name": "A-thread-locals", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Thread local storage (TLS)"}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2019-04-02T06:47:33Z", "updated_at": "2019-04-02T11:59:35Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "OS: Ubuntu 18.04\r\nDoesn't seem to happen on Windows, untested on MacOS.\r\n\r\nI created [`cr-sys`](https://github.com/Neopallium/cr-sys) crate to wrap [cr.h: A Simple C Hot Reload Header-only Library](https://github.com/fungos/cr).\r\n\r\nIt works, except that each version of the plugin isn't unloaded correctly, if the plugin uses TLS destructors registered with `__cxa_thread_atexit_impl`.\r\n\r\nC++ plugins can be compiled with `-fno-use-cxa-atexit` to disable the use of `__cxa_thread_atexit`.  But I can't find away to do this with Rust plugins.\r\n\r\nRight now the only work around is to not unload old plugin and make sure to use a different name for each plugin version.\r\n\r\nIs there any way to run the TLS destructors registered by the plugin or to disable TLS destructors for a Rust shared library?\r\n\r\nRelated issue on `cr.h`:\r\nhttps://github.com/fungos/cr/issues/35\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629/reactions", "total_count": 3, "+1": 3, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/59629/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}